summary: seriously i’ve been fortunate enough to be able to enjoy a lot of great female leads and dynamics between women over the past...
body: seriously i’ve been fortunate enough to be able to enjoy a lot of great female leads and dynamics between women over the past few years especially but nothing… quite has the deliberate feminine energy that killing eve does. nothing else uses its female characters as such a powerful. driving force.  there’s always a male villain or a male love interest or SOMETHING that factors into the motivation in a major way and killing eve is just “but actually our entire world revolves around this magnetic force between these two women”

title: on a more serious note...
body: Killing Eve and Russian Doll are also about childfree women in their late 30s-early 40s for whom being childfree is a choice they made a while ago. It isn’t even really an issue. They have so much living and interesting things to do right here and now that have nothing to do with the wanting or not wanting of kids. They have so much they need from life - so much to take and so much to give. And they’re very different women! But similar in that they are allowed to be prickly, complicated, morally fraught - and considered important by a story. For their pov. Their unique moral/existential journeys. Not for what they represent to someone else.
